            <h2>Welcome To FOODSHARE</h2>
            <p>At FOODSHARE, we are driven by a single, powerful mission: to combat food waste and nourish our communities. We believe that no food should go uneaten while there are people in need. Our platform connects generous donors, such as banquets and event organizers, with local NGOs and food banks dedicated to redistributing surplus food to those who need it most.
</p>
                <br>
                <h2>Our Mission</h2>
                <p>Food waste is a significant issue globally, with millions of tons of edible food discarded each year. Meanwhile, many individuals and families struggle to put enough food on the table. Our goal is to bridge this gap by facilitating the efficient transfer of surplus food from events and banquets to local charities and organizations that can use it. By doing so, we aim to reduce waste, alleviate hunger, and support sustainable practices within our communities.</p>
                <br>
                <h2>How It Works</h2>
                <p>1. Connect: Our easy-to-use platform allows banquet organizers and event planners to list surplus food in real time.
                    <br>
                2. Match: NGOs and food banks in need of food can browse available donations, selecting what best suits their needs.<br>
               3. Transfer: We facilitate the logistics of food transfer, ensuring that surplus food reaches its destination safely and efficiently.</p>
                <br>
                <h2>
                    Why We Do It
                </h2>
                <p>Food waste is not just an environmental issue—it's a social one. By redistributing surplus food, we not only help reduce the strain on our landfills but also provide essential nourishment to those who are struggling. Our commitment to sustainability and community support is at the heart of everything we do.</p>
            
